javac -d <path to copy pacakge> <java file name>

Ex: placing package in current working directory
	>javac -d . Example.java

Ex: placing package in C:\abc directory
	>javac -d C:\abc Example.java

Rule: abc directory should be existed, else it leads compile time error

pacakgeexamples>java pack.Example
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: pack/Example

pacakgeexamples>set classpath=%classpath%;C:\abc

pacakgeexamples>java pack.Example
package demo
